args: Did you find him, Your Highness?
No. I take it you haven't spotted any clues\neither, Elly?
No. It's hard to believe he's been missing\nfor three whole days.
I can't imagine he's actually gone for good\nthough—he left all his things at the castle.
Hopefully he hasn't gotten himself into\ntrouble.
Oy, lookee here! We gots some moneyed\nfops runnin' right at us.
Heh heh. We could rack up a mighty fine\nransom what if we got our hands on ya!
Oy, don't go sayin' words like ＂kidnapper,＂\nnow! I'm a hunter—just that my prey ain't\nyour usual beasts, is all.
And I've been mighty lucky, let me tell ya.\nJust recently, I nabbed myself some feller\nwhat can freeze anything!
You will tell me the location of your lair,\nupon pain of death! Now...ready yourself!
C'mon, let's go skating together!\nIt's loads of fun!
We're going to go and spread the word\ntogether, right?
And since that's the plan, it's essential that\nyou know how much fun it is first-hand.
Yeah, yeah. We all love skatin' so much.\nNow shut up already!
I wish this guy would freeze his mouth\ninstead'a the ground...
We gotta sell him off what before he\ndrives me insane!
Orsem looks rather cheerful for someone\nwho's been kidnapped.
Pffft. Guys probably pretended to be\ninterested in skating and he came with\n'em of his own accord.
Does he not realize he's being tricked?\nUgh, what a credulous man.
Well, at least he's not hurt.\nNow let's go rescue him!
Stop right there, you kidnapping churls!
Eh? Who the heck are you people?!
Huh? Oh, hey, {player_name}!\nWhat brings you here?
You're being tricked! These people have no\nintention of helping you fulfill your dream!
They just want to sell you to someone who\nwants your abilities!
Soooo...you're NOT going to spread the\njoy of skating across the world?
ARGH! SHUT UP ABOUT SKATIN' ALREADY!\nWe only ever cared about yer powers,\nya dumb idjit!
And that's why we'd be real upset if ya\nwas to escape, see? Now outta the way!
Orsem, you have to get out of here!
...Uh, guys? Is it just me, or is the floor\nstarting to freeze in here?
I'm as much at fault for being tricked...\nBut even so, I cannot forgive this...
I can never forgive someone who abuses\nmy skating dream!
Aw, crap! This guy's stupid fast!
H-hey! Don't run off and... AAAARRRGGHH!
And now we come to you...
Well, I suppose that's that.\nOrsem, are you hurt?
Good, because you really had us worried.
It's all well and good to give your all for\nyour dreams, but you need to be a little\nmore aware of what's going on around you.
...I will reflect on this. And I'm sorry\nfor worrying you all.
I don't know what else to say.
Hey, yer okay, so all's well that ends well.\nPlus all the other kidnappin' victims\nseem to be okay, too.
Let's free 'em and get back to the castle.
But do I even have the right to go back...?
